title: Company cutting back on fleet of driverless taxis in San Francisco after crash with fire truck
description: A driverless taxi company is cutting back on its fleet of autonomous cars on the road after a crash between one of its vehicles and a fire truck in San Francisco. NBC News’ Jake Ward has the details.

title: New Orleans Saints tight end Jimmy Graham taken into custody after experiencing a 'medical episode'
description: New Orleans Saints tight end Jimmy Graham was taken into custody after experiencing a "medical episode," on Friday night, according to a statement from the team.

title: New York City councilwoman assaulted by a stranger during 'creepy' live TV interview
description: A New York City councilwoman found herself on the receiving end of an unexpected and "creepy" kiss from a stranger during a TV interview with CBS New York.

title: Meet the Taylor Swift fan who performed the entire Eras Tour live on her TikTok page
description: With the help of her family and friends, Chelsea Biehl turned her living room into a stage and performed the entire Taylor Swift Eras Tour live on TikTok.

title: Biden campaign expects GOP candidates to 'out-MAGA each other' during first debate
description: The Biden campaign plans to highlight what it's calling an "extreme MAGA blueprint" by GOP candidates during the first Republican presidential debate Wednesday.

title: ‘Orphan well’ mishap stirs suspicion and frustration in tiny Pennsylvania town
description: More than a year after an incident at an abandoned well, some New Freeport residents say they are still without definitive answers over whether their water is safe to drink.

title: Britney Spears says she's 'a little shocked' as she addresses Sam Asghari divorce for first time
description: Britney Spears said she was a shocked as she spoke out for the first time since she separated from her husband Sam Asghari after just over a year of marriage.

title: Hot classrooms are impairing student learning and health amid record-hot year, teachers say
description: Some educators said longer periods of hot weather, particularly in places that aren't used to it, are making it difficult to teach and putting kids at risk.

title: LIVE BLOG
description: Forecasters warn of 'catastrophic' flooding as Hurricane Hilary churns toward California

title: Maui wildfire death toll, already highest in modern U.S. history, could surge
description: The windswept wildfires that scorched Maui last week were the deadliest in modern U.S. history.

title: Search underway for Tennessee pair missing in Alaska for more than a week
description: A search is underway in Fairbanks, Alaska, for a pair of travelers from Tennessee who were reported missing a week ago, authorities said.
